purchasedVideos.name: Part 1: Obtaining Police Records & Ethics Presentations
purchasedVideos.description:
The first part of the 2020 Annual Conference,  moderated by Kati Dunn of Canyon City, occurred Wednesday, May 20, 2020. Topics: 
"Obtaining Police Disciplinary Records" Tristen Edwards, Meto PD, and "Ethics: Can I take my client's phone? Ethical Concerns in Processing Client Evidence," by Carl Macpherson, Metro PD, and David Elkanich, Portland.
